<h3>Nuking and Healing </h3></b></center></font>
<br>
<center>
<table bgcolor="black" text="silver" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="1" width="95%">

<td align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="black">
<center>

<table bgcolor="black" text="silver" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="1" width="95%">

<tr><td align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="black">

<font face="arial" Size="-1" color="caffb0"><b>Don't nuke the mob when it is at full health. Let the tank get the mob to hate it, then let the nukes fly. Don't over nuke though.

Same is with healing. Let the tanks get hate before you heal. 

It also is the same with backstab. With the new aggro changed I have noticed mobs hate me more. I try and wait until the tanks engage the mob after pulling and the mobs hp starts to drop, then I drop a backstab. Usually I try and get evade, lowers aggro, not by much =( Anyways, hope this helps.</b><br></font>
<br><br>

</td></tr>



